<div class="container my-5">
  <div class="text-center mb-4">
    <h2 class="section-title">My Service Learning Experiences</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="row gy-4 justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/youtube.jpeg" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="YouTube Workshop for Seniors">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">Service Learning Session 1</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">YouTube Workshop for Seniors</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Volunteer</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Guided seniors in basic YouTube navigation</li>
            <li>Demonstrated volume control and playback</li>
            <li>Explained step-by-step usage</li>
            <li>Communicated in Malay to assist Malay-speaking seniors</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br>
            From this experience, I realised that explaining technical concepts in simple terms is crucial when teaching seniors.<br><br>
            I learned to be patient and empathetic, understanding that everyone learns at their own pace and to adapt my teaching approach to suit the needs of each participant.<br><br> 
            This session also improved my communication skills, and ability to engage learners with different backgrounds.<br><br>
            This experience made me more aware of the challenges seniors face when using technology and motivated me to continue volunteering and making a positive impact in my community.
          </p>
             
            
          <p class="card-text">.</p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Teamwork</li>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Teaching</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/piccollage1.jpeg" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="PicCollage Workshop">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">Service Learning Session 2</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">PicCollage Workshop for Seniors</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Volunteer</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Guided seniors to create digital memories with PicCollage</li>
            <li>Reviewed templates, stickers, text and filters</li>
            <li>Provided one-on-one support for seniors</li>
            <li>Communicated in Malay</li>
          </ul>
           <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br> Guiding seniors through the PicCollage workshop showed me that digital creativity can be enjoyed by anyone, regardless of age or technical experience. <br><br>
             I learned to balance giving instructions with allowing seniors the freedom to explore independently, which not only strengthened my teaching skills but also helped build their confidence. <br><br> 
             This session also highlighted the importance of clear and culturally sensitive communication, and using Malay to connect effectively with the seniors improved my ability to engage diverse learners. <br><br>
          </p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Empathy</li>
            <li>Patience</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/chatgpt_workshop.jpeg" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="ChatGPT Workshop">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">Service Learning Session 3</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Introduction to ChatGPT for Seniors</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Participant</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Introduced seniors to ChatGPT basics and practical uses</li>
            <li>Demonstrated tasks like recipes (Nasi Minyak) and learning aid examples</li>
            <li>Explained AI in simple terms and used Malay for clarity</li>
            <li>Presented in English to improve public speaking</li>
          </ul>
           <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br> Volunteering to teach seniors how to use ChatGPT was a meaningful experience that highlighted the importance of making technology like AI, accessible to all <br><br>
            Guiding them through basic tasks of ChatGPT, such as generating recipes helped me appreciate how AI can be used to support daily tasks and learning. <br><br>
             This session also enhanced my public speaking skills, as I took the initiative to present in English to a group of seniors, which was a valuable opportunity to practice clear and effective communication. <br><br>
             Overall, this service learning session strengthened my teaching abilities, public speaking skills and empathy. It has also motivated me to continue to give back to the community by helping seniors learn how to use, explore and benefit from new technologies.<br><br>
          </p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Empathy</li>
            <li>Teaching</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
   <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 d-flex">
      <div class="card service-card w-100">
        <img src="/images/ygos.jpeg" class="card-img-top service-img" alt="YGOS Workshop Session 2">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title fw-bold">YGOS Workshop Session 2</h5>
          <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Sports Engagement for Youths (Game On!)</h6>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Volunteer</p>
          <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Refereed Captain's Ball Games, to ensure fair play and safety</li>
            <li>Participated in sports games like volleyball and badminton with youths</li>
            <li>Engaged in meaningful conversations with youths to create a fun and inclusive environment</li>
            <li>Collaborated with YGOS staff to referee captains' ball while engaging with the participants during the session</li>
          </ul>
           <p><strong>Reflection:</strong><br><br>  
            Volunteering at the YGOS Game On session was an enriching experience for me. It taught me how to create a positive and inclusive environment for youths through refereeing and active participation in the sports games. <br><br>
             Although I am not very athletic, I learned to step out of my comfort zone and referee the Captains' Ball games, which challenged me to stay confident, make quick decisions, and lead the session fairly <br><br>
             Furthermore, engaging with the youths helped me develop empathy, as I adapted my communication style to connect with them better to match their energy. <br><br>
             Overall, this experience showed me the importance of supporting others and creating a fun and positive experience for youths, even if it means stepping out of my comfort zone to take on new challenges. It also strengthened my communication skills and ability to engage with diverse groups of people.<br><br>
             
          </p>
          <p><strong>Skills Gained:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Communication</li>
            <li>Empathy</li>
            <li>Teamwork</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
